<HEADLINE>Chorus-line PCs</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975044617</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
--
THE idea that the late Mark McManus lacked size as a policeman could only come
from someone (Kenneth Wright) who had not (unsurprisingly) seen a police person
(any rank) for some years.
Thanks to discrimination and trendy bigwigs who say height (size) is of no
importance in a hi-tech, well-trained force (hooligans concur), Strathclyde
Police resembles (with some exceptions) the chorus line at the Pavilion,
frightening only those (victims) who unsuccessfully seek protection.
M Reilly,
217 Brenfield Road,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
