<HEADLINE>Susan's double</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>TOM McCONNELL</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975044623</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TWO winners in succession yesterday lit up the gloom for Susan Bradburne at
Edinburgh when Charming Gale and Blue Charm completed a 38-1 double.
These successes ended a lean spell for the Fife trainer. In all it was a great
afternoon for ``the kingdom' with Rocket Run winning for the second time in
seven days, giving Kinross-based Lucinda Russell another success.
Her Fiveleigh Builds, who has won twice, was sent off 6-5 favourite to take the
feature chase. Andrew Thornton took him into an early lead which the the pair
maintained until blundering six out. Charming Gale, always up with the leaders,
was left in front and stayed on to win by six lengths.
Bradburne acknowledged the luck had gone her way, but also praised conditional
jockey Andrew Watt.
Blue Charm completed the double for the Cupar yard when Tim Reed brought the
five-year-old with a run in the home straight to win the Levy Board Hurdle by
five lengths from Triennium.
Wills Telmar, odds-on for the Lasswade Chase, blundering and unseating his
rider when about to make his challenge. Rocket Run led all the way to give
Russell her sixth winner in her first season.
</TEXT>
