<HEADLINE>Any exodus from Norway?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975044626</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A YEAR ago the people of Norway voted to remain independent and retain control
of natural resources like oil and fish. Before the November 1994 referendum
supporters of EU membership warned that rejection would result in a disastrous
exodus of businesses seeking re-location in EU countries.
Although none of the four main parties here advocates full Scottish
independence on the model of Norway or Iceland, it would be helpful if Scottish
electors could be told if any major companies have moved out of Norway since
November 1994, or if any are currently planning to move.
Gerald Quin,
9 McCall's Avenue,
Ayr.
</TEXT>
