<HEADLINE>Glasgow lose Jardine and Logan</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>32</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975044630</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
INJURIES to Stirling County's two capped backs, Ian Jardine and Kenny Logan,
have forced Glasgow to make further changes for the inter-district championship
match against North and Midlands at Beveridge Park, Kirkcaldy, tomorrow.
Jardine has a neck strain, an injury that prevented him from playing for
Stirling in the premiership match against Boroughmuir last Saturday at
Bridgehaugh, and Logan injured a knee in that match, while he was playing at
full back instead of his international position on the left wing.
The place at centre has gone to Tim Sanderson, a district newcomer from GHK.
Logan is replaced on the left wing by his Stirling colleague, Angus Turner, who
has had 13 previous games for Glasgow.
Sanderson is the third newcomer in the team, joining his former Old Anniesland
colleague, Iain Sinclair, the 19-year-old wing forward who is now with
Watsonians, and Guy Perrett, the 20-year-old West of Scotland lock forward.
Chris Simmers, the Edinburgh Academical centre who was omitted from the
district team after the 21-7 win over South African province Griqualand West at
Hughenden three weeks ago, has voluntarily dropped out of Glasgow's squad and
has thrown his lot in with Edinburgh. Glasgow's team is now:
C Sangster (Stirling County); T Mathewson (Glasgow Academicals), T Sanderson
(GHK), A Garry (Watsonians), A Turner (Stirling County); C MacGregor (Glasgow
Academicals), C Little (GHK); J Gibson (Stirling County), G Bulloch (West of
Scotland), G McIlwham (GHK), M Norval (Stirling County), G Perrett (West of
Scotland), F Wallace (Boroughmuir), captain, M Begley (Glasgow Academicals), I
Sinclair (Watsonians). Replacements - H Bassi (GHK), J McLeod (GHK), F Stott
(West of Scotland), J Brough (Stirling County), G Doran (Glasgow Academicals),
C Docherty (GHK).
q EDINBURGH were due to select their side last night to play the Scottish
Exiles at Richmond tomorrow.
The Exiles, however, have already made their choice on the side which kicks off
their title defence. Team:
G Fraser (London Scottish); M Dods (Northampton), A James (Wasps), R Eriksson
(London Scottish), G Smith (Orrell); S Laing (Instonians), D Patterson (West
Hartlepool); D Hilton (Bath), M Scott (Orrell), P Burnell (London Scottish), A
Nesbit (London Scottish), K Stewart (Cardiff), D Blyth (Waterloo), E Peters
(Bath), S Holmes (London Scottish). Replacements - L Mair (London Scottish), M
Smith (Blackheath), N Mitchell (Stourbridge), A Nicol (Bath), G Thompson
(London Scottish), M Craig (Leicester).
</TEXT>
