<DATE>951205</DATE>
<HEADLINE>From hostility to gratitude CLINTON AND IRELAND</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975044631</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Might I be alone in wondering if President Clinton has permitted himself a wry
smile when he considers the lengths that the British Premier and his cohorts
went to in order to attempt to undermine his bid for the White House at the
last presidential election?
I suspect that John Major is now more grateful for the backing and support of
Bill Clinton than ever he dreamed possible just three short years ago.
And wouldn't it be ironic if future historians were to judge Clinton as being
infinitely more adroit in his handling of foreign policy issues than either of
his two immediate predecessors, the Republican Presidents Reagan and Bush?
It's a funny old world, as Lady Thatcher would put it.
Bruce Maclachlan,
1c Rowans Gate, Paisley.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951205-000023</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951205-000023</DOCID>
<DATE>951205</DATE>
<HEADLINE>A grouping of Greens</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975044632</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I WAS interested to see that the SNP proposes an Association of States of the
British Isles after Scottish independence.
The Scottish Green Party is a member of the Federation of European Green
Parties which includes all the national Green parties from the Atlantic to the
Urals.
Within this, the Scottish Green Party, the Green Party of England and Wales,
the Green Party of Northern Ireland, and Comhaontas Glas, the Irish Green
Party, have formed a group to meet regularly to discuss areas of mutual
interest.
Although the UK voting system means that we have yet to make an electoral
breakthrough, the fairer system in Ireland has allowed the Irish Greens to have
people elected at all levels of Government including two MEPs, one TD, and a
Lord Mayor of Dublin.
Dr Eleanor Scott,
Scottish Affairs Speaker,
Scottish Green Party,
8 Culcairn Road,
Evanton.
</TEXT>
