<HEADLINE>Main puts cash on ice</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>32</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975044658</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ICE SKATING
STEPHANIE Main is proving a hot property for professional show promoters. But
the Edinburgh-based skater, who recently won back the British figure-skating
title, has given them the cold shoulder.
Main, 19, who came third in the multi-nation Piruetten '95 tournament in Norway
last weekend and stars in an ice pantomime at Paisley this weekend, wants to
remain amateur to compete in the 1998 Olympics and has turned down several
big-money offers.
q JUST 13 days after the death of double Olympic gold medallist Sergei Grinkov,
the remaining cast of the Discover Card Stars on Ice figure-skating tour
returned to the ice in Lake Placid, New York, to perform in his honour.
Grinkov, who twice won gold partnering his wife Ekaterina Gordeeva, collapsed
and died of a heart attack while practising at Lake Placid.
</TEXT>
