<TEXT>
SNOOKER
PETER Ebdon, losing finalist in the Royal Liver Assurance UK Championship at
the weekend, yesterday found out who his opponent will be in the first round of
the German Open in Frankfurt today.
India's Yasin Merchant will face Ebdon after a 5-0 victory over German Peter
Wagner in the preliminary round. Merchant had breaks of 62, 48, and 38 but
needed a blue-to-black clearance to complete the whitewash.
Of the wild-card invitations, only Belgian Ivan van Velthoven succeeded in
winning a frame. He did so against Englishman Dave Finbow, who rattled in
breaks of 84, 77, and 42 to complete a 5-1 victory and earn a first-round tie
against former world champion Steve Davis.
</TEXT>
