<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<FLAG>Foreign Digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975044678</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
School closes
HARARE: Zimbabwe has closed a secondary school which lost 22 of its pupils at
the weekend when a boat capsized in a lake south-west of the capital Harare.
Education secretary Stan Chigwedere instructed the immediate closure of Moleli
Secondary School - three days before the end of term for this year - to save
other pupils and teachers from trauma.
Search fails
VALLETTA: A search by Maltese, Tunisian, Italian, and US military aircraft has
found no trace of a Maltese plane which disappeared with six people on board on
Sunday. Michael Williams, a Briton living in Malta, was on the aircraft which
went missing in bad weather while on a two-hour flight from Tunis to Malta.
</TEXT>
