<HEADLINE>Action on homes that waste heat</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975044695</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LOWER fuel bills are expected to follow the launch in Edinburgh yesterday of a
computer program to measure energy efficiency of homes.
The National Home Energy Rating Scotland is based on the Building Research
Establishment's Domestic Energy Model.
NHER(S) can take account of higher winds and lower temperatures in Scotland,
and consider different building materials an methods of building. It will
recommend ways of improving energy efficiency in existing properties or new
homes.
NHER(S) works on a scale of 0 to 10, where 10 is the most energy efficient
home. The average NHER(S) in Scotland is 3.3, compared with the UK average of
4.3.
</TEXT>
