<DATE>951205</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Solicitor's appeal is rejected</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975044699</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A FORMER chairman of Dundee Football Club has lost his bid to be reinstated as
a lawyer.
Three appeal court judges have ruled that the Scottish Solicitors Discipline
Tribunal was fully entitled to order that Mr Andrew Drummond be struck off the
roll of practising solicitors for professional misconduct.
Mr Drummond was found guilty of unreasonable delay in handling clients' trusts
and winding up estates, failure to provide accounts, and delay in transferring
assets to beneficiaries. He was also found guilty of misleading the Law Society.
Mr Drummond, who practised under the name of Drummond Robbie and Gibson in
Dundee, argued that his conduct did not justify such an extreme penalty, in
view of the effect on his livelihood.
</TEXT>
