<HEADLINE>Nicholl is the main attraction</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>34</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975044705</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
EXACTLY a week after the anniversary of Raith Rovers' finest hour, when they
won their first major trophy in the club's 112-year history, the Coca-Cola Cup,
manager Jimmy Nicholl was feted in Glasgow yesterday as the Scottish
Professional Sports Photographers Association personality of the year.
The former Manchester United, Rangers, and Northern Ireland player managed to
keep his team on such a high after that magnificent achievement that they won
the first division championship, made it through to the second round of the
UEFA Cup, and are currently fourth in the premier division.
Nicholl was presented with his award at a lunch in a Glasgow hotel where the
main speaker was another famous Fife manager, Jim Leishman, the ex-Dunfermline
leader who is now inspiring Livingston at the top of the third division.
Snappers get it right - P33
