<DOCID>GH951205-000118</DOCID>
<DATE>951205</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Signet adds to services</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>26</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975044727</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PRESSURE on EU farm spending is going to make things increasingly difficult for
many livestock producers, according to a leading farm consultancy.
This makes it all the more imperative breeders and finishers get up to speed on
their farm management systems, claimed Simon Taylor of the Signet farm business
consultancy.
``The decision to retain full livestock compensatory allowances at the same
level as the past two years is just one example of the coming squeeze. Input
costs are also rising as a result of relative shortages of both cereals and
forage crops.''
Mr Taylor, who was speaking on the eve of the launch of a new Signet service at
the Welsh Winter Fair today, said leading producers wanted more farm management
information.
``we have introduced a whole farm business system to ensure the business stays
on course. It is, in effect, a one-stop shopping system offering access to the
top experts in the field.''
</TEXT>
