Golf
OPEN champion John Daly will be the only winner of a major title this year
competing at the Johnnie Walker World Championship in Jamaica next week.
Tournament organisers yesterday confirmed that the three other major winners -
Ben Crenshaw, Corey Pavin, and Steve Elkington - had all declined invitations,
along with the world's two leading ranked players, Greg Norman and Nick Price.
But the top three in the European Order of Merit - Scots Colin Montgomerie and
Sam Torrance, plus Germany's world No.3 Bernhard Langer - will be in the 20-man
field, which has been cut by four from last year.
Nick Faldo, defending champion Ernie Els, and American Fred Couples will also
be in the line-up, 18 of whom are tournament winners this year.
